stylometry: @Risk allows you to run several simulations at the same time, one for each value of some variable.  It also allows you to generate several different outputs at the same time based on the different order quantities to figure out as to how much of should be ordered.  When you run a simulation with 5 inputs, you will get 5 results for which you ran, and it will show you the avg. mean profit, min and max profit and the standard deviation.  When analyzing the data, you want to look for the highest avg. mean profit and the lowest standard deviation when making your decision.
